ğŸ”„ Authentication Flow (High-Level)

User signs up or signs in
Backend validates credentials
JWT is issued and returned
Token stored on client
Token sent via Authorization: Bearer <token>
Backend middleware verifies token for protected routes

ğŸ“¡ API Overview

User Routes:

POST /api/v1/user/signup
POST /api/v1/user/signin

Blog Routes:

POST /api/v1/blog
PUT /api/v1/blog/:id
GET /api/v1/blog/:id
GET /api/v1/blog/bulk
GET /api/v1/blog/me


